</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>ACR21:v96#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="ACR21"/><meta name="dc:title" content="ACR &#xA;              21-&#xA;                CHAPTERED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div width="100%" style="text-align:center;"><div id="bill_num_title_chap"><span style="text-align:center;font-weight:bold;font-size:1.1em;font-family:'Times New Roman'; "><b>
                Assembly Concurrent Resolution
              
                        No. 21</b></span></div><div style="text-align:center;padding-top: 1.0em;padding-bottom: 1.2em;" id="chap_num_title_chap"><span style="font-size:1.4em;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;">
                      CHAPTER 175</span></div></div><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;">Relative to the Galt Police Officer Harminder Grewal Memorial Highway. </span></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center">
                  
                  [<span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Filed with
              </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Secretary of State
              </span> <span style="font-size: 13pt">September 10, 2025.
                      </span>]
                </div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">ACR 21, Flora.
                          Galt Police Officer Harminder Grewal Memorial Highway.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would designate a specified portion of State Highway 99 in the County of San Joaquin as the Galt Police Officer Harminder Grewal Memorial Highway. The measure would request that the Department of Transportation determine the cost of appropriate signs showing this special designation and, upon receiving donations from nonstate sources sufficient to cover the cost, to erect those signs.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">YES</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_EBDFE89F-6155-4530-9F4B-50E65A318BCA"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Harminder Grewal was sworn in as a Police Officer with the City of Galt Police Department on February 25, 2019; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_C2C5EB4A-70CA-47AF-B04D-595216D08F72"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Officer Grewal had an immediate impact during his short career with the Galt Police Department, where his desire to do the best he could each day resulted in awards in his first full year; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_941EA5CC-A270-472B-A5B4-C785569A5AC0"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Officer Grewal was awarded Officer of the Year, a selection by his peers for his work ethic and integrity, which inspired others to perform at their highest levels; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_4965B53F-8C94-490F-847E-DD4277D1103E"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Officer Grewal was awarded the Mothers Against Drunk Driving (MADD) award for 2020 based on the number of DUI arrests he made that year; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_03E4C8C2-30D7-4A1E-80B9-1FA590621CF1"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Officer Grewal served the Galt Police Officers Association as Treasurer, and he was near completion of his bachelor’s degree; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_5E0B88F0-F243-439C-A6B9-B7C5585C0855"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, On Sunday, August 22, 2021, after two and a half years of exemplary service to the City of Galt, Officer Grewal was traveling northbound on State Highway 99 on his way to assist with the Caldor Fire in El Dorado County; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_44B85A45-8D4F-40E2-BD36-14F1E03FFCA6"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Just north of Dillard Road in Sacramento County, a pickup truck traveling southbound on State Highway 99 hit the center median, broke through a barrier, and entered the northbound lanes, striking the patrol vehicle head-on and causing grievous injuries to Officer Grewal; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_7F154AFB-36DF-4872-9919-E09342E1D62D"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Officer Grewal ultimately succumbed to those injuries on Thursday, August 26, 2021; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_13344995-0AB7-4548-B6B4-5B55E448449F"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Officer Grewal, who is survived by his parents, brother, and countless other family, friends, and loved ones, will be remembered for his hard work and dedication to professionalism in law enforcement and profoundly missed by all; now, therefore, be it </div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_40B5412F-C6B7-450B-97B0-4C465BEEF4BD"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Assembly of the State of California, the Senate thereof concurring, That the Legislature hereby designates the section of State Highway 99 between Collier Road Overcrossing 29-137 (Postmile 036.667) and Begin Bridge No Channel Dry Cr 24-30R (Postmile 038.766) in the County of San Joaquin as the Galt Police Officer Harminder Grewal Memorial Highway; and be it further </div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_2BB0B632-EB92-4483-909E-862511624E7B"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Department of Transportation is requested to determine the cost of appropriate signs, consistent with the signing requirements for the state highway system, showing this special designation and, upon receiving donations from nonstate sources sufficient to cover the cost, to erect those signs; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_DE0E3E4D-0FB0-4F05-A47D-EF8ED825FB7A"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly transmit copies of this resolution to the Director of Transportation and to the author for appropriate distribution. </div></span></span></div></body></html>
